      "rationale": "Systematic mesh convergence study performed with four mesh refinement levels (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.5 mm, fine 0.3 mm, very fine 0.2 mm element size at screw root). Richardson extrapolation applied; grid convergence index (GCI) for stiffness QoI = 0.8%, for yield force QoI = 1.1%. Final mesh (0.3 mm at critical regions) selected with discretization error < 2% for all QoIs. Gradation 3 achieved: formal GCI analysis with Richardson extrapolation demonstrating discretization error quantified and < 2%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
