      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/solver-error-level1",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analysis with large-deformation formulation. Newton-Raphson iteration convergence monitored; force residual tolerance 1×10⁻⁴ and displacement residual tolerance 1×10⁻⁴ applied. All load steps converged within 50 iterations. Energy balance checked post-solution; artificial energy < 0.1% of total internal energy confirming no hourglassing or contact stabilization artifacts. Gradation 2 achieved: convergence criteria documented and verified for all solution runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/use-error-level2",
      "rationale": "FEA model setup reviewed independently by two engineers not involved in original model development. Boundary conditions, material property assignments, contact definitions, and load application verified against documented model specification. Independent review checklist completed with zero critical discrepancies identified. Two minor documentation clarifications resolved prior to final run. Gradation 2 achieved: independent peer review of model setup documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/model-form-level3",
      "rationale": "Continuum FEA with elastic-plastic material model (bilinear isotropic hardening, Ti-6Al-4V per ASTM F136 tensile data) and frictional contact (μ=0.3) between screw and UHMWPE block. Large-deformation kinematics enabled. Model form selection justified by comparison of linear vs. nonlinear predictions against experimental force-displacement curves; nonlinear model reduces systematic bias from 18% to 5.1%. Alternative model forms (beam element, rigid contact) evaluated and rejected with documented justification. Gradation 3 achieved: model form selection supported by comparative analysis of alternatives with quantified improvement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/model-inputs-level3",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, tangent modulus=2.2 GPa) sourced from coupon tensile testing of same Ti-6Al-4V material lot used in screw manufacture (N=5 coupons per ASTM E8). Screw geometry imported from certified CAD with dimensional verification against CMM measurements of 3 production screws (max deviation 0.02 mm). UHMWPE block material properties from supplier datasheet with independent DMA verification. Friction coefficient from literature (Bartel et al.) with sensitivity analysis (μ=0.2–0.4) showing < 3% QoI sensitivity. Gradation 3 achieved: all primary inputs traceable to direct measurement with uncertainty characterization."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
