      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from production lot tested across two independent laboratories (Lab 1: n=6; Lab 2: n=5). Screws sourced from same production lot as design submission samples; certificate of conformance documents material and dimensional compliance with design specifications. Inter-laboratory reproducibility assessed; coefficient of variation for stiffness 6.2%, yield force 7.1%, consistent with expected biological and manufacturing variability. Gradation 2 achieved: multiple specimens from production-representative lot tested across multiple laboratories."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/test-conditions-level2",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted per ASTM F1717-21 protocol at single test condition (quasi-static displacement rate 25 mm/min, ambient temperature 22±2 °C, dry condition). Required level 3 for model risk level 3; achieved level 2 because only a single test condition (no rate variation, no wet/dry comparison) was evaluated. This known gap is documented and accepted by the credibility assessment team as a bounded limitation within the declared operating envelope, which explicitly restricts applicability to ASTM F1717 quasi-static ambient conditions. The operating envelope constraint mitigates the extrapolation risk.",
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026/factor/test-conditions"
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/equivalency-level2",
      "rationale": "FEA model inputs directly matched to experimental specimen measurements: screw geometry from same CAD used to manufacture test specimens; material properties from same material lot; boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry (loading block position, constraint locations). Fixture compliance measured experimentally (0.08 mm/kN) and incorporated into FEA boundary conditions. Documented mapping table confirms 1:1 correspondence between 12 key model input parameters and their experimental equivalents. Gradation 2 achieved: systematic parameter equivalency mapping documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
