      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/output-comparison-level3",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison using validation metric E/uval per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3. Validation uncertainty uval computed as root-sum-square of experimental uncertainty (inter-specimen variability, measurement system uncertainty) and model numerical uncertainty (discretization + solver). All three QoIs: stiffness E/uval=0.87, yield force E/uval=1.12, force at 40 mm E/uval=0.74 — all below 1.96 threshold. Full force-displacement curves compared qualitatively showing consistent shape and failure mode. Gradation 3 achieved: formal E/uval metric applied to all QoIs with complete uncertainty budget."
