      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly correspond to ASTM F1717 required reporting metrics and are the primary design performance indicators for pedicle screw fatigue life estimation. Clinical relevance documented: yield force predicts onset of permanent deformation under worst-case intraoperative loading; force at 40 mm bounds post-yield energy absorption relevant to fracture risk assessment. QoI selection reviewed and endorsed by clinical advisor (orthopedic spine surgeon). Gradation 3 achieved: QoIs directly tied to clinical decision criteria with expert endorsement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
