  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepts the FEA model as sufficiently credible for the declared COU subject to the explicit operating envelope and applicability constraints documented in the ContextOfUse. Evidence summary: (1) All three primary QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) pass the pre-established acceptance bounds with E/uval values of 0.87, 1.12, and 0.74 respectively, all below the 1.96 threshold. (2) Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. (3) The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the operating envelope is explicitly restricted to ASTM F1717 quasi-static ambient conditions — the exact condition tested — and the applicability constraint prohibits use of model predictions outside this validated condition space. The operating envelope bounds (axial load 0–2500 N, bending moment 0–15 N·m, temperature 20–25 °C, screw diameter 7.0–8.0 mm) are densely covered by the N=11 validation dataset. (4) Provenance chain is complete from raw experimental data through FEA predictions to validation metrics. (5) Independent peer review of model setup and credibility assessment completed with no unresolved critical findings. The decision is conditioned on: model predictions must not be used outside the declared operating envelope; any design change to screw geometry, material, or manufacturing process requires re-assessment of affected credibility factors.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z",
